text:
â€¢RECIPEâ€¢  If you have tried è†ç”° lor mee, this is similar to that! I got some clams recently and decided to make this because it adds so much flavour to the broth. The broth tastes amazing with so much seafood in a pot. Plus, not much seasoning is needed.

I always thought you need a specific type of noodles but I used the egg noodles from @wulihaonoodles and it goes really well. Pair it with some sambal belachan ğŸ’¯ğŸ’¯. I am going to make this for my family and in laws and I am sure it will be a hit! ===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
â€¢ @wulihaonoodles egg noodles
â€¢ Clams
â€¢ Pork Lard (optional) 
â€¢ 6 prawns
â€¢ A few stalk xiao bai cai
â€¢ Half onion, sliced
â€¢ tau pok, cut into small pieces
â€¢ A few shittake mushroom, sliced
â€¢ 500ml chicken broth
â€¢ 1 tbsp sesame oil
â€¢ 1 tsp soy sauce

METHOD:
1) Pan fry garlic and onion and prawn head till fragrant
2) Add in taupok and mushroom and fry. Add the chicken broth. 
3) Add in condiments and simmer for 5 mins. 
4) Add in clams and vegetable and simmer for 30 seconds. 
5) Add in the noodles and simmer till noodle is cooked. 
6) Drizzle some Chinese wine and serve hot. ============================================================ #oldschool #putien #clans #noodles #15minutemeals #instadinner #instafood #15minutesrecipe #simple #sgig #sgrecipes #sgfoodie #sgfoodies #sgfoodstep #instagfoodsg #singaporehomecooks #homecookedmeals #whati8today #instagfoodsg #å®¶å¸¸ä¾¿é¥­ #sgfoodlover #onepotmeal #comfortfoods #circuitbreakersg

image_desc: Photo by Menus & Venues ğŸ‡¸ğŸ‡¬ on August 29, 2020.
text:
One of our go-tos in #orchard Rd is this Malay-Indonesian restaurant at the top of @tangssg, @dancingfish.sg. Each time we go there, we try something new.

Funnily enough, though they are famous for their crispy "dancing fish", we usually prefer to order meats. Last night we tried their barbeque duck with percik sauce (really excellent) and their oxtail (extremely tender though I found the style a tad too sweet). I love their egg dishes so we had their flossy prawn #omelette. For veg we had #sambal kailan with prawn, which had a great spicy kick. We supplemented these with yellow rice (not shown).

The last time we visited was before #circuitbreakersg, so certainly glad to be back!

image_desc: Photo by @sgplantstories on August 29, 2020.
text:
Breynia disticha 'Roseo-picta'
I've always thought it was a small compact shrub till I saw it looking quite different after #circuitbreakersg . It became tall (about 1.2m here), with larger leaves and a more porous body. It became clear that it's distinctive white and pink new leaves (probably where its variety name comes from) were a result of regular pruning.

This plant is a caterpillar host plant (see the chewed up leaves in pic 2), and has little green flowers hidden among the stems (which passersby will never see ğŸ˜…)

text:
As meimei's childcare started staggering arrival timings for different levels at the start of phase 2 #circuitbreaker, her N1 level got allocated the earliest 7-730am slot.
Mama used to send her in around 9am.
.
Luckily jiejie's primary school also started staggering timings & her P2 level got the 740am arrival timing (from 720am previously).
This meant that papa had to transform into a race car driver, sending meimei in first, followed by jiejie.
.
Those who have kids in childcare know that, sometimes we have to Q to enter, especially with the stringent checks now, the waiting time is prolonged.
There were a few times whereby jiejie's school teacher messaged me to check why she was not in school yet even at 740am. ğŸ¤¦â€â™€ï¸
.
But what to do, because meimei's school is near one of the foreign workers' dormitories & we take the same LRT line as the workers when I send and fetch her, I think it's best that papa still remains a race car driver, for now la.
Most importantly meimei has gotten used to the early mornings so mama can æ”¾å¿ƒ abit.
.

Ingredients for Ramen Broth:â£â£
â¤ï¸2-3 cups prawn/pork broth ( I cooked prawn shells/head, garlic and pork bones in a slow cooker for 8-10 hours) and then strained to get the brothâ£â£
â¤ï¸1 tbsp minced garlic â£â£
â¤ï¸1 yellow onion, chopped into fine piecesâ£â£
â¤ï¸2 tbsp shallots oil â£â£
â¤ï¸5 pieces shiitake mushrooms, soaked to softenâ£â£
â¤ï¸ 7-8 pieces of dried scallopsâ£â£
â¤ï¸1/4 cup milk â£â£
â¤ï¸Red chilli flakes (optional)â£â£
â¤ï¸3 tbsp white/ red Miso pasteâ£â£
â¤ï¸2 tbsp chopped chives â£â£
â¤ï¸1 tbsp cornflour with 2 tbsp waterâ£â£
â£â£
Steps:â£â£
1)In a pot, add 2 tbsp shallot oil and fry garlic and onion until fragrant and garlic slightly brownâ£â£
2)Add prawn/pork broth, dried scallops, mushrooms and let simmer 2-3 mins until onions are soft â£â£
3)Add in milk, miso paste and red chilli flakes and let simmer another 2-3 mins. â£â£
4)Mix cornflour with water and add it to the broth if you want a thicker broth (if not omit this step)â£â£
5)Throw in spring onions and stir for 1 minâ£â£
6)Pour on TOP of cooked Ramen! â£â£
â£â£

Dry Ingredients:
Flour - 60g
Rolled Oats - 2 tbsp 
Baking Powder - 1tsp

Wet Ingredients:
Chia Egg - 1 qty
(1 tsp of Chia Seeds with 3 tsp of water. Let it sit in the fridge for 10 minutes.)
Green Tea/ Milk - 110ml
Coconut Oil - 1 tbsp

Cooking:
Coconut Oil - 1 tbsp

1. Combine Dry Ingredients well.
2. Add in all Wet Ingredients and mix well. Don't over mix.
3. Heat up the pan in medium low heat with the coconut oil.
4. Scooped up one heaping tablespoon of batter and place the batter onto the pan. Spread it into a circular pattern or any shape desired. Let your creativity juices run! :D
5. Flip pancakes.
6. Serve the Pancakes with Pure Honey/ Chocolate and Fresh Fruits.

image_desc: Photo by Pam & Ping | Singapore Foodie in Hock Prawn Mee.
text:
Hungry at night? We decided to try these prawn noodles since its in the central and hurray - its 24hrs!

We tried the prawn soup and the dry prawn noodles with intestines and came to the conclusion that this place is only popular because itâ€™s open late. Also, the dry noodles seem to be preferred as the chilli is the storeâ€™s highlight. Still, itâ€™s not something that we would purposely make a trip down for again.

For a 24hr establishment we expected them to be well stocked with ingredients, but to our dismay, there were no beansprouts or kangkong left for our noodles. Boy, were we glad though that we had arrived earlier because the group that ordered after us did not have pork slices for their noodles - rationing is  probably why their ingredients are not so generous. Soup-wise is slightly better than average where you can taste the prawn essence after hours of boiling - with no fishy taste.

There is a sign indicating that customers could have a 1 time soup top-up, which is great to warm up your stomach at night. When we saw it, we were pleased, but when we asked for the soup top up, we were also given an extra ingredient - an additional eye roll.

Other than that, this place is nothing to rave about - just a late night eatery

Dyed/ cut my hair and it surprisingly looked good Unconsciously became addicted to TikTok Wore the same pijamas for days Rewatched all my favorite TV series'.
text:
Boredom during lockdown has led us to do all kinds of activities to pass the time. The internet saved us by giving us Tiktok, Netflix, Youtube and other streaming platforms to pass the time. Some of us got a little more creative and were inspired by the countless haircutting videos to try and become an impromptu hairdresser. Which of the above have you done while you were stuck at home? Tag a friend and comment below the activities you completed!

On a more serious note, after months of circuit breaker, it is normal to lose our connection to the environment beyond our houses. We may have started feeling socially inept due to the constant isolation. Texting your ex might then come as a safe choice, either out of boredom or vulnerability, or because meeting someone new in the current situation just seems unlikely. 

Kopi Date offers a safe space for genuine connections to form and develop. We invite you to sign-up for a date with us, reconnect with the outside world, and challenge you to a unique experience.

Our S.T.E.A.M. class for preschoolers â€“ Kinder S.T.E.A.M. is one of the very few classes in Singapore that offers a true S.T.E.A.M. curriculum. It is a pre-primary science class, that includes all other aspects of S.T.E.A.M., like technology, engineering, art and math, all rolled into one class. 

In the same class, the children could be dabbling with an experiment involving milk (learning about breaking down of fats in milk), then constructing a robotic arm, using q-tips to create a skeleton art piece, then learning about even and odd numbers in relation to body parts! The general knowledge gained, learning to ask questions, think creatively and problem solve, is what would be highly beneficial in a childâ€™s learning journey. 

Benefits of S.T.E.A.M. in early childhood:
- Develop critical thinking

- Introduces various avenues of learning

A lot of people always commented that I am blessed with thick and long hair. You might not know that I have sensitive scalp and poor health conditions which lead to frizzy hair, hair loss and lots of grey/ white hair. For me, I would say that I am truly blessed with good people and services around me. 

Thanks to @junmingjoonmin and team of @crescendohairdressing 
for taking great care of my #haircut / #haircolouring / #hairtreatment / #hairrebonding and #scalptreatment for coming to 3 years. Using the premium #hairproducts and giving me good advices on #haircare. 

Mucota Treatment is excellent and it does not contain any harmful chemicals like formaldehyde.

I am indulged with the organic hair treatment products and during #circuitbreakerperiod , Jun Ming advised me what kind of hair colouring treatment which I could get from Watson or Guardian Pharmacy and WhatsApp-ed me to arrange appointment once his hair salon could attend to service me again. 

My sincere gratitude towards his kindness, friendship and attentive services. Being a business owner is not an easy journey, I could see his passions, perseverance and politeness towards customers, no hard sell, patience explanation towards some of their requests (I.e. he strongly discouraging me to bleach my hair. He would always tell me â€œI would like to see you having long and healthy hair insteadâ€) 

After #circuitbreakersg , whenever I am at the hair salon, I could see how they take precaution measures by taking temperature, scan QR code, disinfectant the seating area and giving hand-sanitisers to customers. 

Hair salon is an essential personal hair care services industry and important to make customers feel welcome, relax and valued for service. The moment you step out, you will be happy to feel good and look good. Give me a ğŸ™ŒğŸ» if you agreed â˜ºï¸

text:
Swipe right for drool worthy photos!!! 

Itâ€™s salted egg and tomyum feast here @49seats! Really love how flavourful the dishes here âœ¨ .

We had the .
ğŸŸğŸ£ğŸŸFish and Chips with Tom Yum Salted Egg Sauce .
ğŸ£ğŸ¦ğŸTom Yum Salted Egg Pasta with Chicken Cutlet (Level 49 Spicy) .
ğŸ£ğŸ’¥Salted Egg Popcorn Chicken .
ğŸ¬ğŸ¥¤Sour Plum Cola .

Ok so for both main dishes I ordered Tom Yum and Salted Egg sauce and... no regret at all âœ¨âœ¨âœ¨ This sauce really is something else guys.. the creamy, aromatic sweet and tantalising salted egg sauce joined forces with the bold yet fresh and slightly tangy and spicy tom yum. Soooo good!! If you havenâ€™t try this combo, please try it soon. They really complement each other harmoniously â˜€ï¸âœ¨ .

The fish and chips is soo big tho! ğŸŸğŸ£ğŸŸ Its deep fried perfectly making it has this crispy golden brown colour exterior! The fish itself is breaded with breadcrumbs and still so tender, juicy and tasted fresh ğŸ˜‹ its served in a bed of straight cut fries and generous amount of tom yum salted egg sauce with prawns and mussel .

For the pasta ğŸ£ğŸ¦ğŸ we just gotta go with level 49 spicy ğŸŒ¶ğŸŒ¶ Happy that i could still endure the heat, tho admittedly i drank after my 2nd bite ğŸŒ¶ğŸ§Š Aside from adding more spicyness to the sauce I noticed there are more chilli padi too in here! This dish really wakes me up and served with huuge chicken cutlet, mussel, prawns and lala! .

Popcorn chicken also has a generous amount of sauce which i loved! ğŸ£ğŸ’¥ i like that the size of it just nice âœ¨ not to big that it will distract the experience, but also not to small that you could only taste the batter âœ¨ .

Aand i found my new fave drink too, sour plum cola! ğŸ¬ğŸ¥¤its fizzy, sweet sour and slightly salty. Definitely it will quenches your thirst after a delectable meal here âœ¨ .

We had #kagoshima ramen from #menyasanji Tanjong Pagar last night. We had actually intended to go to #hakataikkousha across the street, but there was a bit of a wait and we were too hungry / impatient. 

So we decided to go to the empty ramen restaurant nearby â€“  a warning sign I guess? Maybe I ordered the wrong dish, but I must say I was a bit disappointed. Hub's #tonkotsu broth was decently rich but my #blacksesame ramen (2nd pic) was really quite bland. The soup wasn't even very hot, and the pork, while generous, was tough and chewy. Noodles and ramen egg was decent. 

Their saving grace was the gyoza, which was tasty and juicy ğŸ¥ŸğŸ¥ŸğŸ¥Ÿ. Anyway, now I still want to go to the other ramen place, which we haven't been to since #circuitbreakersg. Oh well, maybe next week!

PHASE 2 DAY 65 -

One activity that we are thankful that reopened was SWIM.

JO LOVES THE POOL.
I remember him bugging me everyday during #circuitbreakersg when he can go back to swim. When phase 2 happened and then swimming was OK to resume, we jump back in almost immediately.

I think it's not so much about 100% safe anymore... But how do we carry on with life and adapt with the COVID-19 situation. We are constantly observing and never complacent about our decisions. We just have to weigh everything and make the best call we can ever make.

I'm glad that even before COVID-19 happen, AquaBambinos have already been very cautious about hygiene, sanitation, temperatures and even class size.
This period is not easy and we surely hope we can all ride through this and emerge stronger than before. ğŸ’•

text:
A sweet pink, deep blue and crystal white colour combination necklace doubling up as a mask chain, this piece took much effort and time in the making. 

The focal necklace piece is made of 3 pink polygonal Morganites (17-18mm) with carved clear quartz in between, followed by iridescent deep blue Swarovski pearl, rose quartz and another iridescent white Swarovski pearl  interlaced with faceted glass rondelles.

The rest of the chain is made up of faceted 5mm moonstone, lapis Lazuli and rhodochrosite, painstakingly double-looped and linked all the way to the 2 lobster clasps.

The interesting thing about this piece is that the focal necklace piece can be removed and easily replaced with another design later on , similar concept to Pandora charms. However, you will have to get Hokeizus to customise another design it for you!

We are pledging 20% to @HPHPcommunity and @Mettacats_and_Dogs_sanctuary,  for every piece sold, DM for details.

text:
â€¢RECIPEâ€¢  Too tired to cook for dinner after a long meeting. Made an old school dish and a soup and we have a comforting dinner in less than 30 minutes! 
===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
â€¢ 2 potatoes, sliced or cubed
â€¢ 150g minced meat (seasoned with 1tsp cornflour, 1 tsp sesame oil, 1tsp soy sauce) 
â€¢ 1 tbsp oyster sauce
â€¢ 1 tsp dark spy sauce
â€¢ 1 stalk spring onion
â€¢ A dash of pepper 

METHOD:
1) Pan fry some potato till both sides are slightly browned 
2) In the same pan, add in some garlic and fry till fragrant. Add in the minced meat and mix well. Add in the condiments
3) Add in the potatoes and mix well. 
4) Add some water and simmer for 2 minutes or till potatoes softens. 
5) Add in the spring onion before serving and mix well.

text:
Look at these lovely sweet treats from @nowbakerysg ! From their signature blancmange roles to hokkaido vanilla cream cupcakes and double flavor classic chocolate and almond coffee cake, each of them had very soft and moist sponge and flavorful fillings.

I especially loved their signature coffee gula melaka rolls ($14.90) because of the thick, rich blancmange filling, which is like milk pudding. The intense aroma of coffee and gula melaka was very pleasant, and the aftertaste of this roll was much lighter than other cakes.

The hokkaido cupcakes ($15.90) were another attention grabber due to its fluffy outer puffs loaded with creamy vanilla fillings. These puffs really reminded of the moist cakes I had in Japan due to its high quality fresh vanilla cream.

The classic cakes ($17.40) came in two flavors, chocolate and almond coffee and these were much for dense and heavy compared to the swiss roll. Chocolate cake was very fudgy and thich, which went very well milk and the coffee cakeâ€™s faint scent of almond was especially pleasant.

Kong Bak Pau conveniently made thanks to @gimpohfoodsg ! 

These amazing â€œcookedâ€ braised pork belly arrive frozen at your door step so all you need to do is just heat them up before you eat! I briefly simmered mine for 10 mins and it was as good as freshly cooked kong bak pao. 

For the buns, I steamed them using the rice cooker for 8 mins and it came out to be soft and hot, just nice for my pork belly. Adding cheese on my braised pork belly buns was extremely delicious as well.

The handmade prawn balls also came in frozen state that were already deep fried, so just toss them on your air fryer for 10 mins and they become very crispy outside and moist inside! They went very well with chilli and mayonnaise as wellğŸ™†ğŸ»â€â™€ï¸

text:
Amazing pork and beef pies from @mypiesp 

This rich, hearty shepherd's pie had very generous fillings made up of seasoned minced meat and assorted diced veggies, that was topped with perfectly baked mashed potatoes. The pie was very soft and creamy, each mouthful being flavorful and filling. This wholesome pie is made from scratch using the freshest ingredients and it was delivered hot so it tasted even better. @mypiesp specializes in three different pie flavors (pork, beef and chicken), and I just love how they don't try to save on the ingredients because the pies are literally loaded with fillings. My personal favorite was the beef pie because it went so well with the creamy mashed potatoes!

Beautiful brownies from @bakked.sg 

These flavorful Blackout Brownies are absolutely chewy and fudgy. 

Although the plain ones were already nice enough due to its thick and rich chocolate-y flavor, my favorite was the Speculoos brownies! The caramelised cookie dough at the core of the brownie gave the right sweet-salty touch, bringing the flavor of this delicacy to a whole new level. 

The Black Forest had a very interesting flavor as well, due to the dark pitted cherries at the core of the brownie. 

All of the brownies were very smooth and moist, and I liked microwaving them for 10-15 seconds to have it warm, which was absolutely delicious. 

Although I usually have my brownies with milk or coffee, I tried them with one of @bakked.sg 's Colonial Tea Blend, which was a fragrant Earl Grey tea. 

The scent of chamomile and citrus was very soothing and surprisingly went well with the sweet brownies.

text:
These crispy chillis from Thailand are extremely addictive! 

No preservatives and MSG have been added to these roasted, all natural chillis and they come in varieties of flavor. 

I started with the original flavor and because these chillis have been deseeded to reduce the spiciness, they didn't have the overwhelming "hot" taste. 

The Mala Crispy Chillis had the nice "numb" effect after every mouth so if you are a fan of mala, this is definitely the flavor you want to try. 

My favorite was the Cheesy Cheese flavor because the cheese powder went extremely well with the spiciness of the crispy chillis. 

The bestselling Tom Yum flavor had the addictive tangy sour taste and because these are low in calories, I felt less guilty finishing half jar at one sitting!

text:
@twobakeboys just introduced new amazing flavor to their tea crepe cake menu and it's one of the best crepe cakes I've tasted in Singapore!

This creamy Thai Green Tea Crepe Cake (S$35 for 6") is made with Thai green tea imported directly from Thailand, leaving no artificial aftertaste in every flavorful mouth.

Each thin crepe layer is covered by thick, rich green tea cream that isn't overly sweet and the generous amount of cream in each layer makes the whole cake extremely smooth. 

Although the cake itself is already good enough, adding the green tea sauce brings the flavors of the cake to a whole new level. 

The gooey bitter-sweet green tea sauce makes the cake even more moist and delectable.

If you are a fan of crepe cakes and green tea, this amazing confectionery is definitely a must-try. They also have a Thai Milk Tea flavor which is another eye-catcher.

text:
I havenâ€™t had that many sourdoughs in my life but @farineaffair Cheddar Rosemary ($15) is now my favourite. Adding a beautiful depth of flavour, the pockets of savoury cheddar was fragrant and intensified with the hints of rosemary. The cheddar wasn't too sharp in my opinion and provided an umami quality too. Deliciously and subtly tangy, the sourdough was surprisingly soft in the middle with a slight chew and a fabulously crunchy crust. However, great on its own, the toast tasted even more sublime with Farine Affair's compound butters!

Made with a mixture of herbs, spices, and other condiments; the Cafe de Paris Butter ($14.80 for 125g) was so aromatic. Herb-tastic, it is best served with toasted sourdough but also good with steaks. With gentle earthy notes, the Porcini Butter ($11.80 for 125g) lends a somewhat meaty flavour that is very addictive as well and goes superbly with toasted sourdough, pasta, broiled proteins, and even steamed vegetables.

text:
Can you guess what Mottainai means? 

"Mottainai is an ageless Japanese wisdom of interacting with the world such that we fully appreciate what exists, treat it as precious and make full use of its potential."

The concept of Mottainai is to harness the potential of recycled organics through scientific innovation and methods such as reducing landfill, re-using olive and carrot by-products, recycling carrot leaves, respecting our animals and reconnecting with nature. 

The spirit of @mottainai_lamb is in its sustainable food production, where food is produced to nurture and sustain. How inspiring is that!

4 days left to the launch of the extraordinary Ottoman Lamb Burger!

Most of the time our prayers are for the 5Cs - comfort, cure, career, courtship and children. God listens to every single prayer with great delight and understands the troubles of our hearts. ğŸ¥°

Philippians 4:6 tells us not to be anxious about anything, but in everything through prayer and petition, with thanksgiving, to present our requests to God. While it is good to pray for our needs, we can become more kingdom-focused like Apostle Paul.

His prayers were heavily centred around God's will and work in His world. He prayed for wisdom, to live out the gospel, to stand firm in Jesus Christ and for gospel proclamation. ğŸŒ

As a church, may we become more kingdom-focused by continually praying more for wisdom, our walk with God, to stand firm in Christ and to proclaim the gospel. ğŸ—£

Itâ€™s Climate Action Week by @msesingapore ! Running until 21 August, this yearâ€™s program covers topics including food sustainability, composting, urban farming, plastics and energy efficiency.

Hereâ€™s one that particularly caught our eye â€” a discussion with @nlb.singapore and @wwfsg on rethinking our relationship with plastic in our shopping habits and daily life. 

Eye popping facts from the event blurbâ€¦ Did you know that Singapore households have generated an extra 1334 tonnes of plastic waste during the circuit breaker? Thatâ€™s the weight of 92 double decker buses! 

Also, the frequency of households who bought their groceries online has jumped by 50%! Imagine how much extra packaging waste has been createdâ€¦ 

If you, like us, are interested about this topic, come join the webinar this coming Thursday, 20th August (7-8pm) through the link in our bio! ğŸ˜‰

text:
// 5 days. That was the only runway we had to prep all our 7 x daily shows at the start of #CircuitBreakerSG in April this year for the launch of @getactivetv as the Covid-19 pandemic hit Singapore hard. 
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
From ideation of each of the individual shows, to the preparation, execution and running of daily operations. From hosts, to talents, crew and staff all working together.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
It was a mammoth effort to pull it off, a crazy one never done before in my life, and I have a stellar cast to thank for pulling through. 
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Over the course of the next few weeks, I will be mixing in throwbacks and some funny behind-the-scenes footages taken from the past 5 months into this IG journal of mine, to go with motivational posts and photos of everyday friends and people I hold dear to my heart.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Thank you for being a part of my life, and for making 2020 bearable.

image_desc: Photo by Noobwifepantry on August 18, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'BEEF FRIED KWA TEOW'.
text:
â€¢RECIPEâ€¢  A comforting meal in less than 15 minutes. 
===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
â€¢ 400g kway teow
â€¢ 150g beef (seasoned with 1tsp cornflour, 1 tsp sesame oil, 1tsp soy sauce) 
â€¢ 100g bean sprout
â€¢ 3 eggs
â€¢ 1 tbsp minced garlic
â€¢ 1 tbsp fish sauce
â€¢ 1 tbsp soy sauce
â€¢ Dark sauce to colour 

METHOD:
1) Add some oil and heat beef over high heat. Remove when it's almost cooked. 
2) In the same pan, add in some garlic and fry till fragrant. Turn to high heat. Add in the kway teow and stir fry when the oil starts smoking. 
3) Add in the condiments and mix well. 
4) Push the kway teow aside and add some oil. Add in the eggs and mix well.

text:
@saltedandhung // Really appreciating all the catch-ups and good food (ie, not my own cooking) now that #sgrestaurants have opened (with appropriate contact-tracing, temperature-taking, social-distancing requirements).

#saltedandhung was very much better than my untrustworthy memory purports to recall - exquisitely balanced, umami bomb flavours that these words + photos fail to adequately convey:
1. 1BITE -CHEESEBURGER 
wagyu #beeftartare, beef fat smoked ketchup, pickles

2. 1BITE - uni umami panna cotta, yuzu, pickled radish, kelp oil, nori cracker

3. 1BITE - FISH & CHIPS
chickpea chip, pea pureÌe, caviar

4. TIME, LOVE & PATIENCE
IPA #sourdough, #whippedlard with chilli oil, #wakamebutter 

5. TREASURES OF THE SEA
#rawscallops, #caviar, yuzu sake, chilli granita

6. SURF & TURF
crayfish, lemonade & charcuterie broth

7. HEART & SOUL
housemade charcuterie - duck breast, bresaola, ?

8. THE WHOLE FISH
Pearl #grouper, #bonecrumb, charcoal 
Kinda #nosetotail but with fish flesh and bones and skin. Especially cool: #fishbone roasted then infused with local soy sauce for a month. After that the bones are dried and blended to a powder. 

Will experiment with this if/when we have another #circuitbreakersg.

9. HOMELAND
#kangaroomeat, beetroot, cauliflower 
Woah, so tender and tasty. Iâ€™d look at the local roadkill a little differently next time weâ€™re doing road trips Down Undah. Kidding.

10. MEAT, BONE & FIRE
wagyu #tritip, bone marrow, ash
That pear and shiitake reduction with bone marrow butter? Superb.
.
Right use of #modcuisine - where the medium (dehydrated things, powders (not used:gels, foam)) does not overshadow the message (properly cooked food with balanced punchy flavours).

As the birthday girl said at regular intervals throughout the meal: â€œeverything Iâ€™ve put in my mouth has been good!â€.

So much in this world that is so delicious!

text:
A half for your better half? Love to dine out but hate bringing half empty bottles?

Or to open one for solo drinking but detest putting them back in your wine cellars? 

Try this little sweetheart from a property with some v royal flair ğŸ‘‘ and at a lovely price point.

Domaine de Baronarques is an old estate, dating back to the 17thÂ Century, when it was called Domaine de Lambert. 

The estate changed several hands in the interim over the next two centuries. It got its rightful place and was transformed when in 1998 the Rothschilds of First Growth Chateau Mouton Rothschild acquired and reinvigorated the estate.

Over the next 5 years, the Rothschilds poured their heart, money and passion to return the estate to its rightful place and to its modernÂ  day glory.Â 

Located in Languedoc,Â in the commune of Saint-Polycarpe, near Limoux, the Domaine is a single 110-hectare (272-acre) estate, 43 hectares (106 acres) of which are planted with vines.

The vineyard is subject to the climatic influence of both Atlantic and Mediterranean oceans, ensuring optimum sunshine and balanced rainfall. Also close to the Pyrenees, the parcels are at an altitude of 250 to 350 metres, tempering the summer heat.

In 2003, Domaine de Baronarques was also awarded the AOC Limoux rouge appellation, newly created by the Institut National des Appellations dâ€™Origine (INAO).Â 

A blend of 48% Merlot, 22% Cabernet Franc and 7% Cabernet Sauvignon, 13% Syrah and 10% Malbec. Ageing is in 25% new and 75% 1-3yr old oak barrels.

 The wine has a lovely nose of black fruit aromas, rose, tobacco with hint of chocolate and vanilla. Offers v polished tannins and a wonderful long finish.

$42/- per btl (usual $47/-).Â Â

text:
How should you start drinking Kombucha for the first time? ğŸ¤©

Well the answer is simple. Our belief is to go slow. We craft our Kombucha to be palatable for everyone (kids included). 

Start with half a glass, poured over ice cubes and observe how your body feels a few hours after. (Enjoy them with tonic/sparkling water if the taste is too strong for your liking) 

If your body reacts well to it, go ahead and gradually increase your consumption! You may experience symptoms like tummy aches, flare-ups and even body aches that occurs due to toxins being encouraged to leave your body! 

If that happens, drink plenty of water and get some rest in before slowly easing back into small amounts of Kombucha after your body grows acclimated to it.

We encourage you to drink them in the morning, on an empty stomach to best experience itâ€™s benefits. However, there is no precise time in which Kombucha must be consumed. It can be consumed in the morning as an extra morning boost during a work out, in the afternoon to combat that office lull or in the evening after dinner as an alternative to sugary desserts!

text:
The first time when we were offered a big sized parcel of Chateau Brane-Cantenac, the classified second growth property from Bordeaux, it seemed such extreme value, we rejected the offer thinking it was too good to be true. 

You can forgive us for this judgment error. You see, we were coming from a round of buying Pichon Lalande and Cos d'Estournel bottles from 1996, 2009s and 2010s. The price to value of Brane-Cantenac vis-a-vis other classified 2nd growth seemed almost ridiculously unbelievable. 

And yet that is how it has been over the last decade. 

Chateau Brane Cantenac is no longer in the shadows of some of its illustrious neighbours yet the bottles across the top vintages '05, '09, '10, '15, '16 offer the best value among second growth bottles.

The wines have always been rated v well over the last decade. So we are always on the look out for offers on these.

The Lurton family that runs the estate has owned Brane-Cantenac since 1925,. The Grand Vin comes from a single parcel of 40+ hectares.

They have also partnered with the academia for decades and extensively carry out their own research: be it wine making, or vine grafting & growing, oak ageing or modern practices in cellar management.

As Jane Anson from Decanter described it post a vertical tasting at the Chateau in 2018, "Brane is never the most showy of wines and yet it has become one of the most sought-after names in Margaux, impressing through the most beautiful layering of aromatics and textured, confident fruits, perfectly encapsulated in the 2005 and even the undervalued 2012."

2005s can be yours for $185 a bottle (normally $205). Just the last few bottles.

text:
During #circuitbreakersg, we discovered that all the fish in this pond had likely been decimated by kingfishers, making it a dengue hazard.
.
But pet shops werenâ€™t allowed to sell any â€œpetsâ€ then. They were however, said the uncle with a knowing nod, allowed to sell food for pets. And so we acquired a $1 plastic bag of #feederfish that were destined for a short life either due to dodgy genes or fulfilling their destiny as some petâ€™s #livefeeder lunch, whichever would be the earlier. 
.
â€œDonâ€™t be too happy; will die soon ah,â€ said the petshop uncle cheerfully as he waved goodbye to me and the bag of #mollyfish.
.
Turns out they were rather tenacious #mollies, and instead of self-destructing after a few weeks, have flourished and even propagated.
.
No idea how the fry survived since the Internet says the fry need to be separated into a #breederbox or risk being eaten.
.
And actually, no idea what the mollies eat since we havenâ€™t ever fed them. Hopefully, their omnivorous diet includes all extant mozzie larvae.
.
Could be an inspirational metaphor for tenacity in a time of pandemic, recession, job losses, world conflict, environmental crisis. Or could be a visual parallel of #Matthew6*. 
.
Now we need to acquire some algae dudes to clean those walls.
.
.
.
*
â€œLook at the birds of the air: they neither sow nor reap nor gather into barns, and yet your heavenly Father feeds them. Are you not of more value than they?
And which of you by being anxious can add a single hour to his span of life?
And why are you anxious about clothing? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow: they neither toil nor spin, yet I tell you, even Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.
But if God so clothes the grass of the field, which today is alive and tomorrow is thrown into the oven, will he not much more clothe you, O you of little faith?
Therefore do not be anxious, saying, 'What shall we eat?' or 'What shall we drink?' or 'What shall we wear?'
For the Gentiles seek after all these things, and your heavenly Father knows that you need them all.
But seek first the kingdom of God and his righteousness, and all these things will be added to you.â€ (Matthew 6:26-33)

image_desc: Photo by ğŸŒˆRainbowDiariesâ­ï¸Shub in â¤ Home Sweet Home â¤ with @shub_sg, @socialmediamomsg, and @homelyconnect.
text:
ğŸ’»ğŸ–±ï¸ğŸ–¥ï¸ Work from Home First Hand Tips ğŸ–¥ï¸ğŸ–±ï¸ğŸ’»

Under the #newnormal many of us are working from home full time or at least partially under staggered work arrangements. We all have appreciated some unlikely benefits of Lockdowns but at the same time, Working from Home is not that rosy especially for health ğŸ˜’

Here are my 2 cents on making the most of the #wfhlife while maintaining health quotient high.
â¬‡ï¸â¬‡ï¸â¬‡ï¸
ğŸ“FOLLOW THE ROUTINE - When we are #wfh there is natural tendency to slack. Since we don't have to get ready, commute and go to the office, we tend to get a bit casual about time. To avoid this slack, it's best that we follow some routine. Get up on time, have breakfast, take shower and look presentable for meetings sets the ball rolling for an active day. 
ğŸ“GET ADEQUATE SLEEP - Disruptions in the sleep time and duration has been one of the major challenges that I faced in the initial days of #circuitbreakersg . Just because we are at home doesn't means each night becomes #netflix night ğŸ˜± I have made it a point that I get at least 6-7 hours of #beautysleep even while WFH.
ğŸ“DRINK ENOUGH WATER and keep yourself hydrated - When I am at home, I tend to drink less H2O and that's not a good habit. So now what I ensure is that there is always my @thermos_singapore on my table. Water is life even during #wfhlife 
ğŸ“EAT MODERATELY - Working from home means snacking more and eating more ? Yes very much possible so to avoid become a balloon it's good that we control the tongue. Eat lesser quantity of food and include lots of #greens and #fibre 
ğŸ“MOVE - There's always a danger of becoming a couch potato that's prone to attract Weight gain, UTI, bloatedness, gastric and many more lifestyle diseases. So what I do is - go on long walks with my hubby, go for grocery shopping, go and sweat it out in condo gym at least a few times in a week. #moveitmoveit 
ğŸ“CREATE CONDUCIVE WORK FROM HOME ENVIRONMENT - If possible, get a separate room, comfortable chair and table and ergonomic devices like this laptop stand from @homelyconnect that helps me to keep #rightposture 
.
What's your mantra to keep fit while WFH? Share with me ğŸ’š
.
#rainbowdiaries #newnormal2020 #doyourbest

image_desc: Photo by Vanessa Kou in Singapore with @soulsugarbakes.
text:
Having gone a little bananas over the many bakes I had bought last month, I completely forgot to post about @soulsugarbakes Banana-tastic Soul Box! At $25, each dessert box comes with 3 Soul Sugar Cookies, 3 Banana Bites, a levain New York-style Red Velvet Cookie, and a jar of Banana Pudding.

Pretty hefty, their Red Velvet cookie â£â£breaks apart to yield a soft interior withÂ generous chunks of white chocolate, a hint of cocoa and vanilla. A tad sweet (even for me), the richness of the molten chocolate after warming the cookie was slightly overwhelming to finish in one sitting. Hence, I would recommend sharing or perhaps balancing it with bites of theirÂ Soul Sugar Cookies.

A classic chocolate chip cookie done right, the Soul Sugar Cookies were made with brown butter and flaky sea salt. Soft and chewy, theyÂ were not too richÂ and the dash ofÂ saltÂ really helped to accentuate the bits of chocolate studded in theÂ bakes.

However, my favourite item was none other than their Banana Pudding which is marketed as the first of its kind in Singapore. Layered with Regal Marie biscuits, the chilled golden pudding was creamy, luscious and each spoonful brought backÂ childhoodÂ memories of me dunking the exact biscuit into warm milo. Though theÂ biscuitsÂ became soggy, the best part is having them absorb all the flavours and lending the dessert a pleasant vanilla taste. I could also get bits of mashed bananas in every bite and overall it wasnâ€™t too sweet.

A close second after the pudding, the Banana Bites were really good too. The buttery muffins were surprisingly moist, light, fragrant, and best enjoyed warm. Mixed in with chocolate chips and shredded coconut, the banana flavour is less pronounced in comparison but had a great texture. The crunch from the coconut and the small pockets of sweetness from the chocolate was the icing on the cake.

image_desc: Photo shared by The Nyonya Sisters on August 10, 2020 tagging @sleeloveforothers. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'THREE TIPS TO MAKING EXERCISE SIMPLE The Nyonya Sisters @THENYONYASISTERS'.
text:
Beginning an exercise program can be intimidating if you have never incorporated regular exercise before or if you havenâ€™t engaged in regular exercise for an extended period of time. Here are three simple tips to incorporate an exercise plan into your TR90 program.

1. Start out easy. Gradually working into physical activity helps you avoid getting too burned out after the first time. Muscle soreness often accompanies novel physical activity, and easing into a new activity can help to prevent this discomfort. Try start out at 15 to 30 minutes for 3 to 5 days a week, and then gradually increase the intensity and frequency.

2. Have a plan and stick to it. Having a plan removes the guesswork from exercise. It becomes easier to accomplish if you already know what you are going to do and how long you are going to do it. Your daily schedule can become busy quickly, and scheduling physical activity into your daily routine ensures you donâ€™t leave it out when time gets crunched.

3. Finally, pick an activity you enjoy. The more you dread the activity, the more likely you are to leave it out of your busy schedule. Walking or jogging enjoyable routes, aerobics or zumba classes, or bike riding are great ways to exercise in an enjoyable way. Whatever activity you select, consistency is the key. By being physically active 30 to 60 minutes most days of the week, it becomes easy to add the benefits of exercise to your weight management efforts.

text:
â€¢RECIPEâ€¢ Wanted to try using my grill pan for something different. I made my own Pepper Lunch! The  LO asked for salmon and the family loves it! I am going to try making with shabu beef the next time round. The sauce is enough for at least two rounds so you can store it in a bottle and refrigerate for next round! Swipe to see my sizzling pan! ===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
â€¢ 5 cloves garlic, minced
â€¢ 1/4 onion, cut into small pieces
â€¢ 50ml soy sauce
â€¢ 50ml honey
â€¢ 2 tbsp oyster sauce
â€¢ 1tbsp slurry (1 tsp cornflour with 1 tbsp water)

METHOD:
1) Fry the garlic and onion till fragrant.
2) Add in the rest of the sauce and slurry and simmer for about 5 to 10 minutes till the onion softens.
3) Use a blender and blend the mixture till you get a smooth solution. Add the amount you like onto your rice.

image_desc: Photo by Belanja Eat in Singapore. May be an image of text that says 'Belanja Eat Need a FREE meal? IMPORTANT UPDATE Please read!'.
text:
It's been 4 months since we first launched Belanja Eat. We started this as a community-led initative, with the intention for it to serve as a stop gap for those in need of a meal during these tough times, while helping out our neighbourhood hawkers. Thank YOU for coming forward to get this going, you have shown us that kindness is still alive and well in our community.
From 10 Aug onwards, the Belanja Eat team will stop updating and monitoring of the Belanja Eat map and stall directory, our social media accounts, our email address and feedback form.
However, we do hope this initiative will still continue for as long as there are meals being Belanja-ed out there! If you know of others who need support beyond just a meal, do check out supportgowhere.gov.sg for available grants and funds for those hard hit by #Covid19 or otherwise.
***
IMPORTANT
For Belanja Eat stall owners:
- If you would like to continue with Belanja Eat after 10 August, please do! The Belanja Eat poster will still be available for download on our website.
 If you are still using the existing poster with the BE team contact details (QR code and WhatsApp number) at the bottom, please fold it down as they will no longer be monitored. Note that the BE team will not be updating the stall directory on our Belanja Eat map or any feedback support after 10 August.
- If you would like to stop Belanja Eat on 10 August, simply take down the Belanja Eat poster on 10 Aug, when you close for the day.
***

image_desc: Photo by Fawn Labs in Jewel Changi Airport with @pei02, @petriebelle, @cambriant, @christina_meiwei, and @eldredquek. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
Happy 55th Birthday Singapore. Be Strong, #Singapore. #foundernotes 

Being featured in this year's National Day Parade show as a protagonist and profile is a huge honor, something I had not expected when we started the "Bottle Project".

Since we returned to the lab in Phase 2 of #CircuitBreakerSG, I am hopeful for change. Change in our society and #Singapore because I have witnessed so much strength, graciousness and have seen so many acts of kindness from fellow Singaporeans. The acts of heroism and sacrifice from our frontline workers and essential workers motivates me everyday to see how and where we can contribute.

I always stress that our "Bottle Project" wouldn't have been if not for the COLLECTIVE efforts and contributions from the Community. Each and everyone of you who walked in to drop of 1 or 2 bottles. YOU contributed in the fight against #Covid-19.

So to all my fellow #Singaporeans, contribute in anyways we can, every little bit is part of a larger Collective effort that will help us rebuild our beloved country as we try to find our way out of this pandemic. #togetherwearestronger 

I am extremely humbled to lead an incredible team here at Fawn Labs. Team mates who have shown leadership, strength, humility and resilience. They have sacrificed their own time and sleep to support this vision of giving back because we have the lab and capability to contribute. The reason why I work so hard everyday since we decided on taking up "Bottle Project" during Covid-19 and other Sustainable projects is because I want to ensure voices like theirs is heard.

Here at Fawn Labs, we believe in building a safe environment to share and learn, a journey to empower each other and raise awareness on issues related to #Sustainability and #CleanBeauty. We want to impact communities with the right knowledge and we want to give back where we can. To start with a ripple and watch it grow into a wave and beyond.

To each and every #Fawnling who has supported and encouraged us through this period, I thank you from the bottom of my heart. We welcome all of you to come and join us on this journey.

Fawn Lab's Family: @eldredquek @cambriant @petriebelle @meiwei11 @pei02

I am very proud of this product.

Did this in Phase 1 for @mm2singapore 's "Love within" challenge! Though I didn't win, I am glad I can now share this! The way I feel about this film can't be changed by criticism and not winning, and I'm glad I've made something I felt genuinely proud of.

A huge thank you to those who helped me here and there with my artistic wants and my technical needs: @sheamisenmusic, @partybells_ @joshuachristiantan @kloudyclown, @haikelzambri. You guys helped elevate my film to this level and I'm so grateful.

This was a story I wanted to tell after hearing about a close friend's struggle. And I can't believe I pulled off this film almost entirely by myself with limited equipment, filmed on a phone, picking up editing skills along the way, acting directing, lighting and writing this piece.

The cherry on top of those struggles was being 1st AD and locations manager because I have 8 people living in my house( it's truly difficult) with loads of stuff lying around and I never would have thought I could pull this off.

Please do like and share this short film if you enjoy it! It goes a long way.

text:
Grilled Chicken
When you see a whole grilled chicken on my feed, it means "I am not in the mood to cook, but I want good food". I have seldom made grilled chicken as a special dish, its always been a quick thing where it takes 5-10 min to marinate, and the rest of the work is done by the oven ğŸ˜† But if the marination is reasonably ok, you get a good meal.
This one ... stuffed it with carrot, potato, lemongrass, onion, ginger, garlic. Marinated in lemon juice, ginger-garlic paste, my favourite 5 spice powder, salt, honey and a tbsp of youghurt to bring all the ingredients together.

Been thinking of Pasta al Limone after seeing @thekitchenettetales Angie's post last week. Haven't had this almost forgotten flavour for a long long while. And yes ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ I support her to include pasta as breakfast staple because Pasta is Life ğŸ˜†

Sharing another under 30-min recipe here.
ğŸ Bring a pot of water to a boil. Add salt & pasta. Cook pasta according to the timing indicated on the packet. Drain well & reserve some of the pasta water.
ğŸ Melt butter with olive oil in a pan. Sear the duck breast skin side down till crisp. Flip over and cook for another couple of minutes or so. Remove & let it rest for a while before slicing thinly.
ğŸ Using the same pan sauteÌ mushrooms until slightly softened, add chopped garlic. Stir fry till the garlic turns light brown before pouring in cooking cream.
ğŸ Let it simmer for a little before adding lemon zest & juice. Add cheese and let it thicken slightly.
ğŸ Add the cooked pasta, freshly chopped parsley, sea salt, black pepper and a few tablespoons of pasta water (if required). Mix well to coat the pasta evenly.

image_desc: Photo by Unapologetically Amanda Koh on August 07, 2020.
text: During the 3 months of the CB, this was a view I thought about, when Fitness First said they were going to dissolve the existing schedule and that there would be changes to the routine that had been ours for years. As a freelance yoga teacher for the last 15 years, we find ourselves in situations like these every now and then, but in my entire lifetime in this, itâ€™s never been as drastic and long drawn out as 2020 has been. I have learnt to embrace the fact that class cancellations are not in fact, a loss of income, but that a predictable source of income has been disrupted, and that I have the freedom to create new ways to manifest what I need. I have learnt that no matter how long I have had classes on schedule or students, that they are not my classes and that I do not have ownership of my students or their practice. I have also taught long enough to know that the ones who find connection, will find their way back if we are meant to journey together again. I have learnt that newness always presents itself, and to be ready to let go to allow the new in, and for that to happen, I have to constantly evolve to serve the purpose that is my lifeâ€™s work. The way I teach today is almost completely different from what I was doing at the beginning of my journey, and yes, I see myself doing this probably for the rest of my life. I have had to start from scratch several times over, and each time teaches me that in evolving, I grow resilience, calmness and clarity. #singaporeyoga #2020vision #fitnessfirstsg #sgyoga #tittibhasana #sunset #fusionopolis #circuitbreakersg #lifein2020 #resilience #weareinthistogether #yoga

image_desc: Photo by Noobwifepantry on August 06, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'TOMYUM SEAFOOD STEW'.
text:
â€¢RECIPEâ€¢ Ran out of idea what to cook and the hubb says: Clear the fridge! Got a pack of tomyum herbs and I made Tom yum stew! So good and easy for a comforting dinner. See IG video for the steps :) ===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
â€¢ A packet of Tom Yum herbs from @fairpricesg
â€¢ 1. 5 tbsp tomyum paste
â€¢ Cooking cream
â€¢ 1 tomato, cut into 4 slices
â€¢ A packet of bunashimeiji
â€¢ 2 tbsp fish sauce
â€¢ Seafood of your choice

METHOD:
1) Fry the lemongrass, shallots and galangal in a little oil till fragrant
2) Add in tomato and mushroom and fry for another minute
3) Add in tomyum paste and enough water to cover all the herbs and boil over high heat for 10 minutes. 
4) Add in more water and bring to boil. Add in the seafood. 
5) Continue to simmer for another 5 to 10 minutes. Add some cooking cream to thicken it. Season to taste with some fish sauce. 
6) Drizzle some lime juice. Serve hot.

My first time checking out Paradise Classic at Jewel. The restaurant serves mainly Singapore and Malaysian zi char mainstays. I must say the dishes we tried were all very good. Very homely and comforting fare and I'm already making plans to bring my parents to try the food as I write this.
.
These are the items we tried, and they are only available for a limited period, which is a pity because though ought to be mainstays!
- Pan-fried Vermicelli with Assorted Seafood $16.80
- Stewed Roasted Pork with Diced Chilli in Claypot $16.80
- Stir-fried La-La in Curry Sauce $16.80
- Seafood Paradise Signature Creamy Butter Crab $88
.
The fried vermicelli is definitely a must try. Love the smoky savoury flavour of the gravy and the texture of the noodles. A dish well done. And the crab! Some will not like the sweet butter sauce but I loved it. I had 3 bowls of that sauce and I polished off 3 mantous too. The crab was sweet and succulent too, and the flesh came out easily. If not for the pricing, I would love to have this again.
.

text:
ğŸšA Super FLAVOURFUL VERSION OF Japanese Fried Rice ğŸš Do you know that adding Kewpie Japanese mayo to the rice before frying makes the taste richer. It also separates the grains so you end up getting those grains well coated with the egg and ingredients you fry them together with â¤ï¸ğŸ’¯ğŸ’¯â£
â£
Ingredients:â£
1 cup cooked riceâ£
1-2 tbsp kewpie Japanese mayoâ£
Spam/ham, chopped into cubesâ£
1 tbsp olive oil â£
2 eggs, lightly beatenâ£
1 tbsp soy sauceâ£
Chopped spring onionsâ£
â£
Steps:â£
1)Mix the rice with the mayo â£
2)In a frying pan under medium heat, fry the spam until skin is slightly crispyâ£
3)Move spam to one side of the pan and add oil to the other sideâ£
4)Add in beaten eggs and cook, scrambling them along the wayâ£
5)Add in rice and mix everything togetherâ£
6)Add in soy sauce and taste. Add more if not salty enoughâ£
7)Add in spring onions and mixâ£
8)Serve warm and top with seaweed (optional)â£

So since I've no talent in drawing, I decided to go for YouTube where many talented artists posted their artworks or even best; TUTORIAL! ğŸ™ˆ So I was browsing through & came across this YouTube video by @makoccinos. It was easy to follow & I managed to come out with a slightly better piece than ever. ğŸ’œ Drawing is really very relaxing for me & I really hope I could improve better the next round.

text:
â€¢ A S S A M  F I S H  H E A D  C U R R Y â€¢

Itâ€™s not everyday that @nikvoon and my cravings intersect, so when they do, I definitely make it count. Nik: â€œHmmm fish head curry sounds goodâ€ Pat: â€œDoneâ€.
.
.
.
My inner uncle gets a huge kick out of buying fresh whole fish over the counter from the fish monger. Nothing beats the value of a whole fresh fish. The selection that day was a little limited but I managed to get my hands on a nice medium-sized white snapper as well as a slightly larger grouper head. Iâ€™m the only one in my household who actually eats the heads in fish head curry, so more for me!
.
.
.
The distinct tang of the Assam lifts and cuts through the rich curry which was balanced out with a smidge of grated palm sugar (instead of plain olâ€™white cane sugar) for an added depth of sweetness - a worthwhile experiment. This curry goes great with fluffy white rice and some freshly fried up papadum for good measure (this isnâ€™t an Indian curry, but why not right?).
.
.
.
Fun fact: Nyonya style Assam Fish Head Curries donâ€™t use any kind of milk/dairy, but instead they use toasted jasmine rice thatâ€™s grounded fo a fine powder.
.
.
Made by me, shot by him.

text:
Gastrogig, a local events and gastronomic curator has recently launched Thank-Goodness-Itâ€™s (TGI), a delivery-only pop-up concept that will change its offerings every 2 months. This first edition of TGI features Chef Shen Tanâ€™s Nasi Lemak from Shen's days at Maxwell Food Centre. Available on www.tginasilemak.com till 30 August 2020, the familiar flavours of her Nasi Lemak are further enhanced with produce from Gastrogigâ€™s 350sqm garden, which make up the bulk of the raw ingredients for the rempah of the rendang dishes. 
*
Featured here (swipe right) is the $88 Makan for 4 set, comprising:
+ Twice Steamed Nasi Lemak Rice + Omelette + Ikan Bilis + Rainbow Pickles + 2 types Sambals
+ Choice of Chicken or Beef Rendang
+ Choice of Crispy Chicken or Crispy Pork Belly 
+ Choice of Sambal Goreng or Sambal Eggplant
+ Dessert: 2 Pieces Pulut Hitam Cake + Gula Melaka Butterscotch
+ Dessert: 2 Pieces Double Valrhona Choc Fudge Cake 
*
Super love the beef rendang! Such robust flavours. I had it for leftovers again the next day and it was still good. Wish I could have tried the pork belly. Desserts good too! Those of you who like sambal will also want to check out the coffee sambal, yes you heard me right. Bottled sambals are also available for order.

text:
Washing, drying, and storing of plates and utensils were one of the many challenges we faced at the stall. Things got worse when the cleaning service fee doubled their pricing back in 2018. We were forced to make the change to use disposable plates and utensils instead.

Of course, we too understood the importance of sustainability and the pollution caused using plastic packaging daily but then came Covid-19, and everyone viewed single-use packaging as a better packaging alternative from a hygiene point of view. We were actively sourcing for a sustainable option but prices for most eco-friendly packaging were not very pocket friendly for us. 

But today, we are happy to share that we found THE option! Using new sugar cane fibre boxes that donâ€™t cost the earth each time you indulge in our biryani ğŸ˜‰ We also encouraged customers to bring their container to enjoy takeaway discounts at the stall and help reduce the use of plastic packaging on earth.

Tiny steps to help make the world a better place. What do you guys think?

No Monday blues thanks to this jumpsuit! ğŸ’™

Things are starting to look up in Singapore and Iâ€™m pretty hopeful for the rest of the year. Not hopeful about travel back home to the USA, as any leisure travel still seems many months away, but just hopeful that we wonâ€™t need to lockdown again. Masks are mandatory here and we check into everywhere we go with our ID and a QR code. It took a while to get used to and get the kids onboard with mask-wearing (kids above the age of two need to wear them) but they were pretty excited about their storm trooper face shields and are used to all the hand washing and sanitizing. We can have up to five people in our house so play dates are back on which has been a game changer for the kids. They love being able to see their friends, and frankly I love getting to see mine. Things are slower but thatâ€™s actually been a really nice change. After that 145 day stretch at home, our family is relishing these little victories.

image_desc: Photo by Noobwifepantry on August 01, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'AF BAKED SALMON'.
text:
â€¢RECIPEâ€¢ Bought a slab of salmon and decided to try baking it with some ingredients found at home. You know it's good when your LO keeps asking for another helping. The photos did not do the dish justice cos I took the pictures hastily as my friends were waiting for lunch. I love the outburst of flavour when we cut open the baking paper before serving. You can add some wine to enhance the flavour too! ===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
â€¢ 1 slab of salmon
â€¢ 1/2 potato, sliced thinly
â€¢ 1/2 onion, sliced thinly
â€¢ A few cherry tomato, halved
â€¢ 3 cloves garlic, minced
â€¢ 1 stalk coriander, minced finely
â€¢ Olive oil

METHOD:
1) Spread the potato, onion and lay salmon on top of 2 pc of baking paper
2) Add the cherry tomatoes, garlic and coriander. Drizzle a generous amount of olive oil on the fish
3) Seal up the fish in the baking paper
4) Place it in the AF for about 12 min at 200 degree celcius. 
5) Remove and cut open the baking paper. Serve hot.
